-In the case of B-Stock or Ex-Shop items, <b>you must notify us straight away if you are unhappy with your item or else we will not be able to offer a refund</b>. If the item is used following receipt, we will not be able to refund the item. Any cosmetic defects relating to the item are made clear in the item description, so if you are unhappy with its appearance <b>you will have to pay for the return postage</b>.</p><p>
-Any items deemed to be faulty by the customer must not be returned before first contacting us. We will contact you within 1 working day to offer a solution. Sending images of the fault where visible can help to speed up this process. <b>An item cannot be refunded or exchanged if used by the customer until an inspection has been made by ourselves.</b> If the problem is repairable, we will send the item back to you free of charge in full working order. If the item is deemed faulty, we will provide further advice. <b>If the item is proved to be faulty, we can also refund up to £10 of your return postage.</b></p></font></pre><font size="2">
